<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870603-0108 </DOCNO><HL> Preferred Issue PlanFiled by InternationalThomson in Canada</HL><DD> 06/03/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> T.ITOSTOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK) </IN><DATELINE> TORONTO  </DATELINE><TEXT>   International Thomson Organisation Ltd. said it filed a preliminary prospectus with the Ontario Securities Commission to issue four million preferred shares, valued at 101.1 million Canadian dollars ($75.5 million), in two series.    Thomson, a publishing, energy and travel-services concern, said McLeod Young Weir Ltd. and Wood Gundy Inc. will buy two million Series I preferred shares at 25.568 dollars each. The shares can be converted into cash in 1991, at the holder's option.    The company also said it will sell two million Series IV preferred shares to McLeod and Wood Gundy for 25 dollars each. These can be converted into cash in 1995, at the holder's option.    The company said proceeds will be used to help finance acquisitions in the information and publishing businesses in the U.S. </TEXT></DOC>